The paper deals with the performance analysis of a wireless communication system, specifically a mixed RF/FSO system with a backup RF link. This involves the study of channel models, outage and error probabilities, and the effect of various system parameters on performance. These topics are typically studied in the fields of information theory (cs.IT), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), communication and security (cs.COMM), systems and control (cs.SY), and physics (cs.PHY).
